Comment: English opening...has a bit of reputation of being a relatively dull opening...this is mainly due(i think) to the little bit of patience needed to build up and is not as hairy as Sicilians....!!

..standard development so far. White is threatening d4 and build up pressure on the Q side. Black will usually counter the finachetto of an English with c6, Be6 and Qd7 to create a weakness on the K side. This is typically followed by f5 and further attacks. White typically needs to eliminate the Nf6...
